```

The regex check is cheap: a full page starts with `<!DOCTYPE` or `<html>`.
Anything else is treated as a fragment and wrapped. This is the right place
because `parseDocument` is the single entry point for all HTML into the pipeline.

No changes needed to `mod.ts`, `cli.ts`, or any other `src/` file.

